## `pub fn update_size(conn, inode, size, mtime_ns, ctime_ns) -> Result<()>`
<!-- checksum: rust-nodes-6 -->

### Purpose
Set `size` and bump `mtime`/`ctime`. Called by blob write/truncate paths.

### Implementation Notes

```rust
pub fn update_size(
    conn: &Connection, inode: u64, size: u64, mtime_ns: i64, ctime_ns: i64,
) -> Result<()> {
    conn.execute(
        "UPDATE nodes SET size = ?1, mtime_ns = ?2, ctime_ns = ?3 WHERE inode = ?4",
        params![size as i64, mtime_ns, ctime_ns, inode as i64],
    )?;
    Ok(())
}
```

