## `pub fn change_nlink(conn, inode, delta: i32, ctime_ns: i64) -> Result<u32>`
<!-- checksum: rust-nodes-7 -->

### Purpose
Atomically add `delta` to `nlink` and return the new value. Used by `link`, `unlink`, `rmdir`, and GC logic.

### Preconditions
- `delta != 0`.
- After the update, `nlink ≥ 0` (caller must not over-decrement).

### Implementation Notes

```rust
pub fn change_nlink(conn: &Connection, inode: u64, delta: i32, ctime_ns: i64) -> Result<u32> {
    conn.execute(
        "UPDATE nodes SET nlink = nlink + ?1, ctime_ns = ?2 WHERE inode = ?3",
        params![delta, ctime_ns, inode as i64],
    )?;
    let new_nlink: i64 = conn.query_row(
        "SELECT nlink FROM nodes WHERE inode = ?1",
        params![inode as i64],
        |r| r.get(0),
    )?;
    Ok(new_nlink as u32)
}
```

