## `pub fn delete(conn: &Connection, inode: u64) -> Result<()>`
<!-- checksum: rust-nodes-8 -->

### Purpose
Delete a node row. `ON DELETE CASCADE` automatically removes the inode's `blobs`, `xattrs`, `symlinks` rows in the same transaction.

### Preconditions
- Caller has verified the inode is unreferenced (`nlink == 0` and no open fds).

### Implementation Notes

```rust
pub fn delete(conn: &Connection, inode: u64) -> Result<()> {
    conn.execute("DELETE FROM nodes WHERE inode = ?1", params![inode as i64])?;
    Ok(())
}
```

